Each protection notification center shall:
Operate the protection notification center during all working days;
Provide a locate request identification number to the excavator for each excavation or demolition location request;
Promptly after receiving an excavation or demolition work notification from an excavator, provide to each of its affected operator members the excavator information required by KRS 367.4911(3);
Maintain a list of all its operator member's identities, business address and business and emergency telephone numbers and record this information in accordance with KRS 64.012 with the county clerk of each county where the operator member has underground facilities. The county clerk shall provide this information upon request for the actual cost of providing a copy, to be paid by the requesting party to the county clerk. The county clerk shall assume no liability associated with the receipt of this information from the protection notification center or for subsequent provision of this same information to the requesting party;
Make the operator members information list available to any person for inspection at its place of business without charge or provide a copy of the list to any person for any county upon request for a fee not to exceed the actual cost of providing a copy;
Define and adopt policies and procedures for processing design information requests; and
Provide the person making a design information request a list of identified operators that will receive notification and notify those operators.

The Kentucky Contact Center shall be governed by a board of directors composed of representatives of member operators who are elected by the membership. Board seats may be filled by representatives of the following:
A natural gas provider;
An electric provider;
A telecommunications provider;
A water/sewer provider;
An interstate pipeline operator;
A municipal utility operator; and
An advisory, nonvoting representative of one (1) of the following:
Home Builders Association of Kentucky;
National Electrical Contractors Association;
Associated General Contractors of Kentucky; or
Kentucky Association of Plumbing, Heating-Cooling Contractors.
